-- KKR Acquires Central England Water Group From Alinda Capital
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2013-05-08T15:33:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-08/kkr-acquires-central-england-water-group-from-alinda-capital.html
KKR & Co. (KKR)  acquired South Staffordshire
Plc, a central England water supplier, from Alinda Capital
Partners LLC, the Greenwich, Connecticut-based infrastructure
fund manager said today. Terms weren’t disclosed.  The group’s South Staffordshire Water and Cambridge Water
divisions supply water to 1.6 million residents in the West
Midlands and East Anglia, Alinda said in an e-mailed statement.
The deal with the investment firm KKR was agreed to on May 3,
Alinda said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
